    <item>
      <title>Postbird in Provence</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/postbird-in-provence/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 Jul 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/postbird-in-provence/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team project:&lt;/strong&gt; 2 producers, 5 programmers, 2 game designers, 3 artists, 2 sound designers&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dev time:&lt;/strong&gt; Roughly half a year&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech stack:&lt;/strong&gt; Unity 2019.4, C#, Visual Studio 2019, Perforce, Trello&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platforms:&lt;/strong&gt; Windows / Nintendo Switch&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Postbird in Provence&lt;/strong&gt; is my graduation project at Isart Digital. It&amp;rsquo;s a cute adventure game that was initially developed for Nintendo Switch, making use of most of the features the joycons have to offer (HD haptics, gyroscope, accelerometer&amp;hellip;). It was a nice technical challenge to try to reach 60 FPS on the platform.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Refureku</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/refureku/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/refureku/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solo project&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech stack:&lt;/strong&gt; C++17, libclang, &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ToruNiina/toml11&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xD;&#xA;  class=&#34;inline-flex items-center gap-1&#34;&#xD;&#xA;&gt;toml11&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;svg id=&#34;external-link&#34; class=&#34;h-3 w-3 flex-shrink-0&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; d=&#34;M15 3h6v6m-11 5L21 3m-3 10v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;, Visual Studio 2019, Git, Trello&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target platforms :&lt;/strong&gt; Windows / Linux / MacOS&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jsoysouvanh/Refureku&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xD;&#xA;  class=&#34;inline-flex items-center gap-1&#34;&#xD;&#xA;&gt;Refureku&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;svg id=&#34;external-link&#34; class=&#34;h-3 w-3 flex-shrink-0&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; d=&#34;M15 3h6v6m-11 5L21 3m-3 10v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt; is a C++17 dynamic reflection library I wrote as a personnal project in my free time. The github repository has a (hopefully nice) README highlighting the library main functionalities, as well as a &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jsoysouvanh/Refureku/wiki&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xD;&#xA;  class=&#34;inline-flex items-center gap-1&#34;&#xD;&#xA;&gt;full wiki&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;svg id=&#34;external-link&#34; class=&#34;h-3 w-3 flex-shrink-0&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xD;&#xA;    viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; d=&#34;M15 3h6v6m-11 5L21 3m-3 10v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt; going into more details. There&amp;rsquo;s not much to write here, just check the repository out ;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Lambo&#39;s Tale</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/lambos-tale/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/lambos-tale/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team project:&lt;/strong&gt; 4 programmers, 4 game designers, 3 artists&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dev time:&lt;/strong&gt; 5 weeks (school)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech stack:&lt;/strong&gt; Unity 2019.3, C#, Visual Studio 2019, Perforce, Trello&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platforms:&lt;/strong&gt; Windows&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lambo&amp;rsquo;s Tale&lt;/strong&gt; is a Metroidvania game in which we play as Lambo, a little lamb who&amp;rsquo;s trying to take revenge on the wolf gang which bullied his little sister (yes, the plot is messed up).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/6GjfYDQagJo?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: center;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;iframe frameborder=&#34;0&#34; src=&#34;https://itch.io/embed/760286?dark=true&#34; width=&#34;552&#34; height=&#34;167&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a href=&#34;https://cfazilleau.itch.io/lambos-tale&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            Lambo&#39;s Tale by cfazilleau&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/iframe&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;personal-contribution&#34;&gt;Personal contribution&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Procedural generation level system&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Enemies + AI&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Redaction of a part of the TDD (Technical Design Document)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Camera&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Character&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A part of the player controller (jump snap, enemies snap)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Interaction system (shop, doors, items)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Semi-persistent inventory system&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Arenas logic&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Generic feedbacks system (particles, sounds, haptics, camera shakes)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Pooling system&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;LD gimmicks (doors, keys, destructibles, spikes, pickable items)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Loading screen&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Damage feedback system&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;FTUE (First Time User Experience - Tutorial) gameflow&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Shop&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Assets integration (animations, sprites)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
